com.appboy.models

Interface IInAppMessage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IPutIntoJson<org.json.JSONObject>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IInAppMessageHtml, IInAppMessageImmersive, IInAppMessageZippedAssetHtml
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InAppMessageBase, InAppMessageControl, InAppMessageFull, InAppMessageHtml, InAppMessageHtmlBase, InAppMessageHtmlFull, InAppMessageImmersiveBase, InAppMessageModal, InAppMessageSlideup, InAppMessageWithImageBase, InAppMessageZippedAssetHtmlBase

    public interface IInAppMessage
extends IPutIntoJson<org.json.JSONObject>
    InAppMessageBase is the base model interface for all in-app messages.

    It implicitly defines policy for in-app message fields that can be changed from outside the object.

      • getOrientation

        Orientation getOrientation()
        Gets the preferred screen orientation for this in-app message.

        In-app messages will only display if the preferred orientation matches the current activity orientation. However, there is an important exception for tablets For in-app messages that have a preferred orientation and are being displayed on tablet, the in-app message will appear in the style of the preferred orientation regardless of actual screen orientation.

        Returns:
        the preferred screen orientation for this in-app message

      • getOpenUriInWebView

        boolean getOpenUriInWebView()
        Whether to use AppboyWebViewActivity to open deep links from this in-app message.

        When true, the SDK will make a best effort to use AppboyWebViewActivity to open the deep link.

        When false, deep links are opened using an Intent.ACTION_VIEW intent.

        See setOpenUriInWebView(boolean)

        Returns:
        true if AppboyWebViewActivity should be used to open deep links from this in-app message.

      • logDisplayFailure

        boolean logDisplayFailure(InAppMessageFailureType failureType)
        Logs a display failure on this in-app message. Failures can only be logged once per in-app message instance and should be logged as early as possible in the display process.

        In-app message display failures may affect campaign statistics so care should be taken when logging display failures.

        Parameters:
        failureType - The precise type of the display failure.
        Returns:
        true if the display failure was successfully logged.

        Gets whether this in-app message is a control for multivariate testing. Control in-app messages should not be displayed to users.

        whether this in-app message is a control.
